On 03 Aug 2014, at 15:19, Pascal Thubert (pthubert) <pthubert@cisco.com> =
wrote:

> Good start Carsten=85

Thanks!

> We need to include source routing, talk about fragments etc=85

Fragments are covered in the current draft.

I didn=92t try to include RFC 6554 source routing because I first wanted =
to cover the functionality of the flow label draft, which is WGLCing =
over in ROLL/6man.  Obviously, given the dominance of non-storing mode, =
source routing is important.  Before designing this (probably as a =
separate dispatch type):

=97 Are there packet captures available that we could use as a corpus to =
discuss encoding choices?
=97 What are values of CmprI and CmprE that we are seeing in real =
networks (i.e., that this should be optimized for)?
=97 Do we need the segments left feature, or can we simply discard =
segments in each forwarding router?
=97 Can we use the hop limit field of the encapsulated IP packet, or do =
we need our own hop limit like in the RFC 4944 mesh header?
=97 How is ICMP error message generation done in real-world RPL =
implementations?  How much of that needs to be preserved?

This obviously is a bit more work than covering the information in the =
flow label draft, so I=92m not sure it should be done now given the =
urgency that is being attached to that draft.

Gr=FC=DFe, Carsten


