All,
     I have completed my AD Evaluation of draft-ietf-6lo-lowpan-mib and
only have a few minor comments.  Once these are addressed, I can start
the IETF Last Call.

1. The Security Considerations section uses "NOT RECOMMENDED" as a 2119
keyword.  However, that phrase is not included in the list in section 3.
 I would suggest either adding "NOT RECOMMENDED" to the list in section
3 or change "NOT RECOMMENDED" to "SHOULD NOT" in the Security
Considerations section.

2. Please add an RFC Editor's note in section 4 to update RFCXXXX
(Figure 1) to the assigned RFC number when the document is published.

3. Figure 1 also refers to RFC 2013, which has been obsoleted by RFC
4113.  Any reason for the reference to the old UDP MIB?

Regards,
Brian


